Exemplarily, it would work like this:

(n(Aye)/N(Aye+Nay+Abs)) * 435 and repeat for each side of the vote for the House. [for. nays: (n(nay))/n(Aye+Nay+Abs))] For the Senate, use the percentages initially displayed after a poll closes and based on that calculate the rest alike to the House

OR

Calculate aye and nay based on the same formula as aforementioned but to keep the actual abstention numbers as are for more realistic margins of those answering "present" and calculate final distributions by e.g. subtract half/half from each side to keep the margins right.
